2. **Surface Area of the Circular Base:**
The circular base of the hemisphere is a circle with radius equal to the radius of the hemisphere. The formula for the area of a circle is $\pi r^2$, so the area of the circular base is $\pi (6)^2 = 36\pi$ square cm.

